review_text:
Lovely 1880's farm house has been updated cosmetically and provides comfort and space for a large group. Good communication, check in was easy and flexible due to no booking immediately before or after, ample parking, well stocked kitchen including a nice welcome basket, awesome large dining table with coffee bar area, comfortable beds in bedrooms with ceiling fans.
Biggest negatives: No bathroom on the second floor where 4 of the 5 bedrooms are. Downsides: The towels in the bathrooms are somewhat small (although an abundance of wash cloths were provided) No side tables for some of the beds, no table lamps, and limited outlets for plugging in. The road the house sits on is actually fairly busy and surprisingly noisy even late at night.
One complaint: removing my own bedding and taking out trash when I'm being charged a hefty cleaning fee. (Other places do not require this)
But, it's a beautiful home, in a lovely setting, great for large groups convenient to several towns in the area

The grocery store/restaurant has basics and we were able to get eggs, cheese for quesadillas, and a lemon for some homemade guacomole. I always cook when we are there and the apartment is well stocked with a blender, crockpot, cooking utensils, etc.

We biked the Peace trail to Beloit/back and the Glacial river trail to Fort Atkinson and back. We also hiked the Ice age trail. Jim's communication was always helpful and prompt. I notice the little extras that aren't necessary with an airbnb but convenient. I appreciated the plug ins/USB outlets next to the bed on both sides, the easy keypad entry, the coffee options, the water/snacks/games provided, accessible shower and great water pressure, the fresh flowers, and the restaurants/brewery suggestions. We feel like we made friends in Janesville and look forward to coming back!! Thank you Jim and Marilyn!!

Incredible! I've stayed in airbnb properties in major cities across the country...who woulda guessed that this hidden gem in tiny Janesville, WI would be my favorite??? Every aspect of the stay was great:
- Space and amenities were as described
- Apartment was spotless
- Tons of options for TV...had cable and Roku
- Wifi and internet were fast and reliable
- Neighborhood is beautiful and the house is walking distance to downtown
- Zero noise from neighbors
- Communication was great, check-in/check-out process were quick and painless
- Tons of clean towels, cloths, linens
The final touch that put this over the top was the fully stocked kitchen. I walked in and noticed muffins on the counter and thought to myself, "Oh, that's a nice touch." I unpacked my stuff and was about to head to the grocery store, but stopped to open the fridge quickly to see if maybe there was a bottled water because I was thirsty. The fridge was full...yogurt, water, juice, adult beverages... Then I looked in the freezer and there were pizzas... Then I looked in the pantry and there were snacks from top to bottom. On top of that, the coffee and tea selection was the best I've seen at an airbnb. Jim and Marilyn know how to host.

review_text: We had a wonderful visit! The Overlook at Lake Koshkonong was perfect for us. The open-floorplan downstairs area has a kitchen, a living room with an easy to use and comfy fireplace, and a dining area. There's also a dining table with chairs and a combo Keurig/regular coffeemaker. The upstairs was very cozy too, with a very comfortable larger bed, skylights (with Roman shades for nighttime), another bathroom with a tub, and a large closet space with hangers which was useful for clothing since we were staying for several days. There's a deck on the second floor with seating, which was awesome for coffee on brisk October mornings. The surrounding area is lovely, with the lake across the street, a wooded area behind, and restaurants a short drive away. It's a great location for quick drives to Madison, and during our stay we also visited Milwaukee and the House on the Rock. Our host, Jamie, was super responsive and a pleasure to work with. Thank you for a fantastic experience!

review_text:
Highly recommend Jamie & Kayla's cabin for a 2 person getaway. The place was exactly as described, very clean, everything smelled nice, and had some nice extras (plenty of shampoo & conditioner, makeup wipes, tampons in the bathrooms, a little basket with beach towels, water bottles, sunscreen & bug spray, etc). The deck had a nice little view of the lake, and is bordered on one side by trees, giving it a more secluded and woodsy feel than expected. We loved the bedroom opening up to the deck, and the whole cabin is a study in well used space, as well as being very cute (by far the cutest, most cabin-y place on the street). Wouldn't recommend if you have a toddler or crawler, due to the open stairway and spacing on the deck rail, but it's perfect for 2 people, or 2 adults + a kid old enough to not fall off a deck but young enough to not creep you out sleeping on the little bed 2 feet from you.
The area was very peaceful (we were there during the week).
We also found some good bars & breweries within a 25 minute drive - for some reason there's no public beach on this lake, but there are a few on Lake Mills 25 minutes away. Recommend hitting Sunset Bar & Grill (15 min drive).
